<br>
I have noticed on Allakhazam's that there are some pretty nice drops from nameds in hard adventures. Although, I have never been in a pickup group that could even conceive of completing a hard adventure, would it be out of the question to take a hard adventure with the sole intent of finding those named MOBs and rolling on loot without even considering finishing the mission? Are people that concerned over their win/loss stats that they wouldn't want to do this? Is it even feasible to think that a pickup group could get to and kill those MOBs? How many named MOBs in hard adventures do you think you could take out in a 3 hour period if you had a good tracker and weren't concerned about the win/loss stats? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vagabond>Vagabond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 920<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/6/03 2:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5522.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: LDoN Loot farming</span><hr size=1> People do this yes.<br>
